{"title": "Ex-soldier hopes coming forward will shine light on \u2018routine\u2019 sexual harassment in Japanese army", "tags": "asia", "timestamp": "2022-12-28", "content": "TOKYO \u2013 Fleeing to an evacuation shelter after a tsunami swept through her coastal hometown in Miyagi prefecture on March 11, 2011, a young Rina Gonoi saw first-hand the relief work led by Japan\u2019s military Self-Defence Forces (SDF).\nInspired to be a force for good, the then 11-year-old fifth-grader saw the SDF as her dream job, and joined the army in April 2020."}